# Code Lab Sample Code to Generate CDATA
Samsung Wallet Card is an e-wallet service allows customers to use Samsung devices to clip various digitized contents on Samsung Wallet. Users can add their own ticket, coupon, boarding pass and other types of data into Samsung Wallet using an 'Add to Wallet' link via multiple online channels such as App, Web, E-mail, or Social Media.\
This is a sample code to help partners generate CDATA.

---

## CDATA
Actual payload data in basic JSON format to communicate between partners and Samsung Wallet.\
It follows <i>RFC 7519</i> specification. For more details, visit https://jwt.io

```java
private static final String PARTNER_ID = "[PARTNER_ID]";
public class JwtGenerator {
    
    PublicKey samsungPublicKey = JwtManager.readCertificate("[SAMSUNG_CERTIFICATE]");
    PublicKey partnerPublicKey = JwtManager.readCertificate("[PARTNER_CERTIFICATE]");
    PrivateKey partnerPrivateKey = JwtManager.readPrivateKey("[PARTNER_PRIVATE_KEY]");
    String data = "[JSON_STRING_CARD_DATA]";
}
```

1. `PARTNER_ID` has to be updated by referring to the Partner ID in the partner portal.\
https://partner.walletsvc.samsung.com
2. `SAMSUNG_CERTIFICATE` and `PARTNER_CERTIFICATE` can be found in the Samsung Account Email which tells you that a partner registration has been completed.\
https://developer.samsung.com/wallet/onboarding.html
3. `PARTNER_CERTIFICATE` is a signed certificate from CSR.
4. `PARTNER_PRIVATE_KEY` must have been created during generating CSR.
5. `JSON_STRING_CARD_DATA` is JSON object card data it defined Card data attributes specification.\
Sample data is here: https://developer.samsung.com/wallet/api/wallet-cards.html

Visit the below page for more detailed information.\
https://developer.samsung.com/wallet/api/add-to-wallet-interface.html
---
